{
  "texts": [
    "Few-Shot prompting is a technique where a prompt is enriched with several examples of how the task should be completed.",
    "This is helpful in case one deals with a complex query where there are already concrete ideas or data available.",
    "As the name suggests, these \"shots\" can be enumerated (based on Dang et al., 2022; Kojima et al., 2022; Tam, 2023):",
    "• Zero-Shot prompts: There are no specific examples added.",
    "• One-Shot prompts: One specific example is added to the prompt."
  ]
}